  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM Bosnia and Herzegovina Crisis Response Plan 2021 &#x2013; Resilience Initiative</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building on the lessons learned from the previously implemented Bosnia Herzegovina Resilience Initiative (BHRI), the overall objective of the programme is to foster youth and community engagement for increased resilience and social cohesion in Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH). To this end, IOM is proposing to bolster youth activism and leadership for enhanced civic and political engagement, strengthen voices and actors that promote inclusive narratives, and expand youth participation in decision-making processes for issues that impact them and their communities. Through a small-grants mechanism, the programme will continue to engage with civil society, community leaders, youth (both those perceived as leaders and influencers, as well as those considered at-risk), local municipal actors and relevant institutions. To empower youth to exert positive change, enhance cohesion among social and community groups across ethnic lines, and strengthen the overall resilience of youth, BHRI targets youth individually and at the community level while fostering exchanges and forging of networks between partners and beneficiaries throughout BiH.</narrative>
  </description>
